at|mitche: And that leads me to East's pass of 2@S.  
When pard preempts and I have AK9 of her suit, I raise.  Do not wait!  When you make a delayed raise, you give the
opponents a "fielder's choice."  They can either let you play or look for their own fit or double.   
That is why West wants to show a defensive value, by the way.  East won't be taking a "phantom save" when she knows 
that West has some defense, too.  (Actually, if East raises to 3@S, West will take a 4-level "sacrifice" and make it.)



